{{lang|en|'''Change.org'''}}是由營利组织{{lang|en|Change.org, Inc.}}經營的請願網站。{{lang|en|Change.org, Inc.}}是一家[[美國|美國]]『認證的B公司』，聲稱擁有超過4億用戶並為組織舉辦贊助活動<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thenonprofittimes.com/news-articles/change-org-gets-30-million-infusion/|title=Change.Org Gets 30 Million Infusion|website=The Non Profit Times|publisher=thenonprofittimes.com|access-date=2015-06-23|archive-date=2017-06-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170601223412/http://www.thenonprofittimes.com/news-articles/change-org-gets-30-million-infusion/}}</ref>。該公司總部位於[[加利福尼亞州|加利福尼亞州]][[舊金山|舊金山]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.sfgate.com/living/article/Ben-Rattray-and-Change-org-3781962.php|title=Ben Rattray and Change.org|access-date=2021-10-08|archive-date=2019-01-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190107001723/https://www.sfgate.com/living/article/Ben-Rattray-and-Change-org-3781962.php}}</ref>。該網站用於促進公眾的請願<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://money.cnn.com/2014/12/09/technology/change-org-25-million-investors/|title=Change.org gets $25 million from big names|access-date=2021-10-08|archive-date=2019-03-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190327101804/https://money.cnn.com/2014/12/09/technology/change-org-25-million-investors/}}</ref>  。

以前包括[[維珍美國航空|維珍美國航空]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://storage.pardot.com/37772/47364/Change.org_Virgin_America.pdf|title=Virgin America found brand advocates to enter a new market|access-date=2020-09-19|archive-date=2017-02-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170201235551/http://storage.pardot.com/37772/47364/Change.org_Virgin_America.pdf}}</ref>以及[[國際特赦組織|國際特赦]]和{{tsl|en|Humane Society of the United States|人道協會 (美國)|美國人道協會}}等組織<ref>{{cite news|last=Alter|first=Jonathan|title=For Change.org, a Better World Is Clicks Away|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-09/for-change-org-better-world-is-clicks-away-commentary-by-jonathan-alter.html|publisher=Bloomberg|accessdate=2021-10-08|archive-date=2019-01-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190107001720/https://www.bloomberg.com/tosv2.html?vid=&uuid=993174d0-1211-11e9-96ac-179949d26568&url=L25ld3MvMjAxMi0wMy0wOS9mb3ItY2hhbmdlLW9yZy1iZXR0ZXItd29ybGQtaXMtY2xpY2tzLWF3YXktY29tbWVudGFyeS1ieS1qb25hdGhhbi1hbHRlci5odG1s}}</ref>的公司都在該站點託管和宣傳其請願書。Change.org的既定使命是「授權各地的人們去創造他們想要看到的改變」<ref>{{cite news|last=Farr|first=Christina|title=Change.org CEO shows how online petitions change the face of health care (Q&A)|url=https://venturebeat.com/2013/05/17/change-org-health-petitions/|access-date=2013-10-07|newspaper=VentureBeat|date=2013-05-17|archive-date=2017-07-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170727181536/https://venturebeat.com/2013/05/17/change-org-health-petitions/}}</ref>。Change.org請願書的熱門話題是經濟和刑事司法，人權，教育，環境保護，動物權利，健康和可持續食品。

== 歷史記錄 ==
Change.org 由現任首席執行官本·拉特雷（{{lang|en|Ben Rattray}}）於2007年成立<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/tomiogeron/2012/10/17/activism-for-profit-change-org-makes-an-impact-and-makes-money/|title=The Business Behind Change.org's Activist Petitions|last=Geron|first=Tomio|website=Forbes|language=en|access-date=2019-03-26|archive-date=2019-03-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190326133420/https://www.forbes.com/sites/tomiogeron/2012/10/17/activism-for-profit-change-org-makes-an-impact-and-makes-money/}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url = https://techcrunch.com/2007/02/07/social-networking-for-change/|title = Social Networking For Change(.org)|author = Gonzalez, Nick|publisher = [[TechCrunch|TechCrunch]]|date = 2007-02-07|access-date = 2021-10-08|archive-date = 2018-07-12|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20180712184722/https://techcrunch.com/2007/02/07/social-networking-for-change/}}</ref>，並得到了創始首席技術官Mark Dimas，Darren Haas 和Adam Cheyer的支持<ref name="Veneziani">{{cite news|url=https://techcrunch.com/2007/02/07/social-networking-for-change/|title=Social Networking For Change(.org)|first=Vince|last=Veneziani|publisher=[[TechCrunch|TechCrunch]]|date=2007-02-07|access-date=2011-12-10|archive-date=2018-07-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180712184722/https://techcrunch.com/2007/02/07/social-networking-for-change/}}</ref>。截至2012年2月，該網站擁有100名員工，在四大洲設有辦事處。Rattray 表示，到2012 年底，「他計劃在20個國家/地區設立辦事處，並以其他幾種語言（包括阿拉伯語和中文）開展業務」<ref>{{cite news|url = https://www.nytimes.com/2012/02/05/opinion/sunday/kristof-after-recess-change-the-world.html?_r=1|title = After Recess - Change the World|author = Nicholas Kristof|work = [[纽约时报|The New York Times]]|date = 2012-02-04|accessdate = 2021-10-08|archive-date = 2018-07-13|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20180713020334/https://www.nytimes.com/2012/02/05/opinion/sunday/kristof-after-recess-change-the-world.html?_r=1}}</ref>。2013年5月，公司宣布由 Omidyar Network 領導的一輪1,500萬美元投資，並表示在18個國家/地區擁有170名員工<ref>{{cite news|last=Empson|first=Rick|title=With $15M From Omidyar And 35M+ Users, Change.org Wants To Prove Socially-Minded Startups Can Attract Big Numbers|url=https://techcrunch.com/2013/05/21/with-15m-from-omidyar-and-35m-users-change-org-wants-to-prove-socially-minded-business-can-attract-big-numbers/|access-date=2013-07-01|newspaper=TechCrunch|date=2013-05-21|archive-date=2018-08-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180815091122/https://techcrunch.com/2013/05/21/with-15m-from-omidyar-and-35m-users-change-org-wants-to-prove-socially-minded-business-can-attract-big-numbers/}}</ref>。

2011年，Change.org 聲稱這是「中國黑客」發動的一次分佈式拒絕服務攻擊的主題<ref>{{cite news|last=Branigan|first=Tania|title=Ai Weiwei campaign website 'victim of Chinese hackers'|url=https://www.theguardian.com/artanddesign/2011/apr/20/ai-weiwei-campaign-website-chinese-hackers|work=[[衛報|The Guardian]]|date=2011-04-20|location=London|accessdate=2021-10-08|archive-date=2016-03-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160320165222/http://www.theguardian.com/artanddesign/2011/apr/20/ai-weiwei-campaign-website-chinese-hackers}}</ref>，並且所指控的攻擊顯然與向中國政府提出的釋放藝術家[[艾未未|艾未未]]的請求有關<ref>{{cite web|last=Joffe-Walt|first=Benjamin|title=Chinese Hackers Attack Change.org Platform in Reaction to Ai Weiwei Campaign|url=http://blog.change.org/2011/04/chinese-hackers-attack-change-org-platform-in-reaction-to-ai-weiwei-campaign/|publisher=Change.org|access-date=2021-10-08|archive-date=2013-03-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130310082134/http://blog.change.org/2011/04/chinese-hackers-attack-change-org-platform-in-reaction-to-ai-weiwei-campaign/}}</ref>。2011年，有人提議將說西班牙語的對口網站Actuable合併到Change.org中 。該活動於2012年進行，當時他們批准了Actuable用戶自願加入Change.org平台<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.publico.es/ciencias/397493/actuable-se-fusiona-con-change-org-y-crean-la-mayor-plataforma-de-ciberactivismo-online |title=Archived copy |access-date=2013-08-24 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120228184822/http://www.publico.es/ciencias/397493/actuable-se-fusiona-con-change-org-y-crean-la-mayor-plataforma-de-ciberactivismo-online |archive-date=2012-02-28 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://tecnologia.elpais.com/tecnologia/2011/09/20/actualidad/1316509269_850215.html |title=Change.org adquiere la española Actuable | Tecnología | EL PAÍS |publisher=Tecnologia.elpais.com |date=2011-09-20 |access-date=2016-11-13 |archive-date=2017-06-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170627230612/http://tecnologia.elpais.com/tecnologia/2011/09/20/actualidad/1316509269_850215.html }}</ref>。

2012年，『亞利桑那州立大學』決定禁止訪問 Change.org，以回應學生「埃里克·海伍德（Eric Haywood）」提出的請願書，抗議「學校的學費上漲」。大學官員聲稱「Change.org 是垃圾郵件站點」，並且進行封鎖是「為了保護我們有限且寶貴的網絡資源用於合法的學術，研究和行政用途」<ref name="huffpost">{{cite news|url = http://www.huffingtonpost.com/josh-levy/arizona-state-censors-cha_b_1253155.html|title = Arizona State Censors Change.org|author = Levy, Josh|work = [[赫芬顿邮报|The Huffington Post]]|date = 2012-02-03|accessdate = 2021-10-08|archive-date = 2016-09-11|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160911193433/http://www.huffingtonpost.com/josh-levy/arizona-state-censors-cha_b_1253155.html}}</ref>。

據報導，2012年4月5日，Change.org 擁有1,000萬會員，並且是網絡上增長最快的社交行動平台。當時，他們每天收到500份新請願書<ref>{{cite web |url=https://techcrunch.com/2012/04/05/change-org-hits-10-million-members-now-the-fastest-growing-social-action-platform-on-the-web |title=Change.org Hits 10 Million Members, Now The "Fastest-Growing Social Action Platform On The Web" |publisher=TechCrunch |date=2012-04-05 |access-date=2016-11-13 |archive-date=2018-10-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181002141811/https://techcrunch.com/2012/04/05/change-org-hits-10-million-members-now-the-fastest-growing-social-action-platform-on-the-web/ }}</ref>。2012年5月13日，《[[衛報|衛報]]》《[[英國廣播公司新聞|英國廣播公司新聞]]》和其他消息來源報導，Change.org將啟動英國特定的請願平台，將Change.org與「38度」競爭，英國非營利性政治行動組織<ref>{{cite news|url = https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2012/may/14/trayvon-epetition-website-changeorg-launches-uk|title = Trayvon Martin petition site Change.org comes to UK|work = [[衛報|The Guardian]]|author = Topping, Alexandra|date = 2012-05-13|location = London|accessdate = 2021-10-08|archive-date = 2016-08-12|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160812074903/http://www.theguardian.com/politics/2012/may/14/trayvon-epetition-website-changeorg-launches-uk}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url = https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/technology-18033968|title = Change.org petition site targets UK campaigners|author = Kelion, Leo|date = 2012-05-14|work = BBC News|accessdate = 2021-10-08|archive-date = 2016-07-18|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160718112659/http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/technology-18033968}}</ref>。

2013年8月，《快速公司》（ Fast Company ）的一篇文章報導說，Change.org很快將開始以請願人為特色，「公司首次可以對任何給定的請願書發表公開回應（目前，他們只能對他們也將能夠創建自己的『決策者』頁面，該頁面將顯示針對他們的所有請願書，收集的簽名數量及其狀態。」 在2017年夏季，Change.org上的一份請願書禁止煽動暴力侵害婦女行為的<ref>{{cite news|last=Bluestein|first=Adam|title=HOW BEN RATTRAY'S CHANGE.ORG BECAME A VIRAL CONSUMER WATCHDOG|url=http://www.fastcompany.com/3014809/change-org-petitions-ben-rattray|access-date=2013-10-07|newspaper=Fast Company|date=2013-08-05|archive-date=2017-11-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171112190018/https://www.fastcompany.com/3014809/change-org-petitions-ben-rattray}}</ref>。

2021年6月30日，Change.org表示美国和加拿大的员工大多签署了{{tsl|en|CODE-CWA|团结数码公司员工运动}}代表[[集體協商|集體協商]]的工会授权卡，故Change.org{{tsl|en|Voluntarily recognize|自愿认可}}团结运动为员工代表<ref>{{Cite news|last=Allyn|first=Bobby|date=2021-06-30|title=Change.Org Workers Form A Union, Giving Labor Activists Another Win In Tech|work=NPR|url=https://www.npr.org/2021/06/30/1011387838/change-org-workers-form-a-union-giving-labor-activists-another-win-in-tech|access-date=2021-06-30|archive-date=2021-07-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210701010510/https://www.npr.org/2021/06/30/1011387838/change-org-workers-form-a-union-giving-labor-activists-another-win-in-tech}}</ref>。

== 重要的請願書 ==

=== {{JPN}} ===
摧毀日本色情文化，澳州在2013-2016年期間截獲18批綽特拉的娃娃，指在當地擁有這些娃娃便已干犯《剝削兒童罪》，而高木則以「我是個藝術家」為由反對這些行動<ref>{{cite news|title=Man who creates child-like dolls insists he is an ‘artist’ who stops paedophiles abusing real kids|url=https://www.thesun.co.uk/living/1609617/man-who-creates-child-like-dolls-insists-he-is-an-artist-who-stops-paedophiles-abusing-real-kids/|work=The Sun|date=2016-08-14|accessdate=2021-02-07|last=Barns|first=Sarah|archive-date=2019-07-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190716190932/https://www.thesun.co.uk/living/1609617/man-who-creates-child-like-dolls-insists-he-is-an-artist-who-stops-paedophiles-abusing-real-kids/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。[[Change.org|Change.org]]上亦有反對綽特拉的聯署，發起人於當中寫道「有關人偶並不適合用於預防[[兒童性虐待|兒童性虐待]]」，截至2016年4月11日，其共有超過5万5千萬個簽名<ref name="合法的に手助け"/>。

高木認為這些產品有助戀童者不去侵犯兒童。但金斯大学医学院的心理学家彼得·法根（Peter Fagan）對此表示質疑，指根據臨床數據，它們可能使恋童者更想侵犯兒童。多伦多大学的心理学家迈克尔·塞托則認為其會減低一類型戀童者侵犯兒童的機會，對於另一類型則會增加之<ref name="Can Child Dolls"/><ref name="如何释放"/>。
=== {{USA}} ===
2011年12月，「馬薩諸塞州」[[布魯克林市|布魯克林市]]的四年級學生通過Change.org發起了「Lorax 請願項目」，要求[[環球影城|環球影城]]在其網站和預告片中加入更多環保信息，以宣傳即將上映的電影《Lorax》『 [[蘇斯博士|蘇斯博士]]的孩子們的故事』。網站和預告片缺少該書中的「幫助環境」這一重要信息。請願書收集了超過57,000個簽名，2012年1月26日，工作室將網站「更新為孩子們要求的環保信息」<ref>{{cite news|url = https://www.nytimes.com/2012/02/05/opinion/sunday/kristof-after-recess-change-the-world.html?_r=1|title = After Recess - Change the World|author = Kristof, Nicholas|work = The New York Times|date = 2012-02-04|accessdate = 2021-10-08|archive-date = 2018-07-13|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20180713020334/https://www.nytimes.com/2012/02/05/opinion/sunday/kristof-after-recess-change-the-world.html?_r=1}}</ref>。

2012年2月2日上午，[[紐約|紐約]]23歲的『史蒂夫·格雷』（Stef Gray）在『莎莉·梅』的華盛頓辦事處舉行了新聞發布會，向她介紹了Change.org『莎莉·梅』的成果。全國最大的「私人學生貸款提供商」請願書，已收到約77,000個簽名者。當天下午，該公司更改了寬容費政策<ref>{{cite news|author = Lewin, Tamar|url = https://www.nytimes.com/2012/02/03/education/sallie-mae-to-change-forbearance-fee-policy.html?_r=3|title = Sallie Mae to Change Forebearance Fee Policy|work = The New York Times|date = 2012-02-02|accessdate = 2021-10-08|archive-date = 2016-07-23|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160723103810/http://www.nytimes.com/2012/02/03/education/sallie-mae-to-change-forbearance-fee-policy.html?_r=3}}</ref>。

