== 商業模式 ==
Change.org通過訂閱成員資格模型，在網站上宣傳請願書和眾籌來賺錢<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.smh.com.au/business/companies/why-change-org-s-army-of-davids-is-neutering-more-global-goliaths-20180228-p4z24h.html|title=Why Change.org's Army of Davids is Neutering More Global Goliaths|last=Bryant|first=Nick|date=2018-03-03|website=smh.com.au|language=en|access-date=2018-08-21|archive-date=2018-08-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180821223213/https://www.smh.com.au/business/companies/why-change-org-s-army-of-davids-is-neutering-more-global-goliaths-20180228-p4z24h.html}}</ref>。

Change.org成員每月捐款，以維持該技術以及由運動家組成的小團隊來指導和支持請願者。公司的大部分收入是廣告-發起或簽署請願書的個人和組織，然後介入以將這些請願書宣傳給其他網站訪問者。

迄今為止，Change.org 已經籌集了5,000萬美元，以推動其在業務，技術和媒體領域的使命導向型投資者的發展。在2017年，由『里德·霍夫曼』 （Reid Hoffman）進行的一輪投資推動了向當前商業模式的轉變<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://fortune.com/2017/05/26/reid-hoffman-change-org/|title=LinkedIn Founder Reid Hoffman Invests Big Change In Change.org|work=Fortune|access-date=2018-08-21|language=en|archive-date=2022-04-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220408023848/https://fortune.com/2017/05/26/reid-hoffman-change-org/}}</ref>。

該網站以前通過運行稱為廣告贊助活動的廣告來賺錢，這些廣告是為諸如國際特赦組織<ref>{{cite news|last=Mui|first=Ylan M|title=Change.org Emerges as Influential Advocate on Issues from Bullying to Bank Fees|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/business/economy/changeorg-emerges-as-influential-advocate/2012/01/09/gIQAoCJHLQ_story.html|work=The Washington Post|date=2012-01-24|accessdate=2021-10-08|archive-date=2017-08-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170828201322/https://www.washingtonpost.com/business/economy/changeorg-emerges-as-influential-advocate/2012/01/09/gIQAoCJHLQ_story.html}}</ref> 之類的倡導組織和為合作組織建立名單的服務<ref>{{cite news|author= Martin, Courtney E.|url= http://www.thenation.com/article/164338/you-are-now-now-future-online-feminism|title= 'You Are the NOW of Now!' The Future of (Online) Feminism|work= The Nation|date= 2011-11-02|accessdate= 2021-10-08|archive-date= 2011-11-05|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20111105172710/http://www.thenation.com/article/164338/you-are-now-now-future-online-feminism}}</ref>。2013年5月，網站啟動了「人群推動的請願書」，允許簽署人在請願書籤署的最後階段支付5到1,000美元來推廣請願書。

== 批評 ==
=== 假簽名 ===
2018年，[[昆士蘭自行車公司|昆士蘭自行車公司]]（Bicycle 昆士蘭州）首席執行官『安妮·薩維奇』（Anne Savage）聲稱，Change.org 上澳洲大規模的反自行車請願書上充斥著虛假的名字。她說，[[昆士蘭自行車城|昆士蘭自行車城]]收到的信息表明，許多名字都是由電子「機器人」創造的。Change.org的發言人否認簽名是假的，稱該組織的工程團隊已經仔細檢查了請願書，並確認他們沒有發現任何異常活動<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.couriermail.com.au/news/queensland/massive-anticycling-petition-full-of-false-names-claims-bicycle-queensland-ceo/news-story/fdf3e0dd06aa3343948dce1020df03b1|title=Massive anti-cycling petition 'legitimate'|date=2018-05-31|website=www.couriermail.com.au|access-date=2021-10-08|archive-date=2021-06-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210612004238/https://www.couriermail.com.au/news/queensland/massive-anticycling-petition-full-of-false-names-claims-bicycle-queensland-ceo/news-story/fdf3e0dd06aa3343948dce1020df03b1}}</ref>。

=== 個人信息的可見性 ===
在某些情況下<ref>{{cite web|title=Privacy Policy {{!}} Change.org|url=http://www.change.org/about/privacy|publisher=Change.org|access-date=2012-03-19|archive-date=2016-01-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160117184118/https://www.change.org/about/privacy}}</ref>{{vague|date=January 2015}}，搜索引擎可以找到簽名和其他私人信息，包括電子郵件地址。Change.org運行用於簽名隱藏的系統，該系統僅在用戶在Change.org上擁有帳戶時才有效<ref>{{cite web|title=I want my name off of this petition immediately! : The Change.org Help Desk|url=http://helpdesk.change.org/entries/20272227-i-want-my-name-off-of-this-petition-immediately|publisher=Change.org|access-date=2012-03-19|archive-date=2012-04-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120412112543/http://helpdesk.change.org/entries/20272227-i-want-my-name-off-of-this-petition-immediately}}</ref> 。相反，該平台因沒有提供足夠的信息說明誰簽署了請願書而受到批評； 例如，一種手段來驗證抗議政治人物的請願書已經由其選民簽名，或者該簽名是真實的<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2015-05-29/change-org-is-amplifying-the-power-of-a-signature|title=Change.org Is Amplifying the Power of a Signature|first=Sarah|last=Issenberg|publisher=Bloomberg|date=2015-05-29|access-date=2018-04-15|archive-date=2021-11-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211105203641/https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2015-05-29/change-org-is-amplifying-the-power-of-a-signature}}</ref>。

=== 公司結構 ===
儘管Change.org是使用.org域後綴而不是商業.com的事實<ref>{{cite web|url=https://bcorporation.net/directory/changeorg |title=Change.org |publisher=B Corporation |access-date=2018-12-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181209213541/https://bcorporation.net/directory/changeorg | archive-date=2018-12-09}}</ref>
This has resulted in debate and criticism<ref>{{cite web |title=Is Change.org about Real Change or Just Pocket Change? |url=http://chieforganizer.org/2012/06/20/is-change-org-about-real-change-or-just-pocket-change/ |publisher=Chief Organizer Blog |author=Rathke, Wade |date=2012-06-20 |access-date=2012-07-10 |archive-date=2012-07-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120706125847/http://chieforganizer.org/2012/06/20/is-change-org-about-real-change-or-just-pocket-change/ }}</ref><ref name="changebiz">{{cite web|title=Change Dot Biz|url=http://www.informationdiet.com/blog/read/change-dot-biz|publisher=The Information Diet|date= 2012-02-28|access-date= 2012-07-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190303053539/http://informationdiet.com/blog/read/change-dot-biz|archive-date=2019-03-03}}</ref>，但圍繞Change.org是一個營利性業務這一事實，一直存在爭論和批評 。該網站被指控欺騙用戶，並掩蓋了事實，即「這是一個以營利性動機促使人們簽署請願書的營利性實體」。通過使用Change.org名稱來故意欺騙Change.org。我懷疑普通的Change.org用戶不知道Change.org是一家營利性公司，並且該公司計劃使用提供給他們的聯繫信息來賺錢。

克萊·約翰遜Change.org發言人『夏洛特·希爾』（Charlotte Hill）在2013年9月的《連線》（Wired）文章中反駁了這一批評，他說「我們是一家以使命為導向的社會企業，在帶來收入的同時，我們將收入的100％ 重新投資到了賦予普通民眾權力的使命人們。這不僅僅是我們還沒有盈利，而是我們絕對不是牟利的」<ref>{{cite news|last=Klint|first=Finley|title=Meet Change.org, the Google of Modern Politics|url=https://www.wired.com/wiredenterprise/2013/09/change-org/|access-date=2013-10-07|newspaper=Wired Magazine|date=2013-09-26|archive-date=2013-09-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130929171530/http://www.wired.com/wiredenterprise/2013/09/change-org}}</ref>。

=== 廣告政策 ===
2012年，該網站取消了以前對付費內容的大部分限制。內部文件開始將「客戶」和「合作夥伴」稱為「廣告商」，並指出「只有嚴格被認定為『仇恨團體』的廣告商才被禁止」<ref name="kos">{{cite web|url=http://www.dailykos.com/story/2012/10/23/1149092/-Change-org-sells-out-progressive-movement|title=Change.org sells out progressive movement|first=Raven|last=Brooks|publisher=Daily Kos|date=2012-10-23|access-date=2015-09-30|archive-date=2015-10-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151001232045/http://www.dailykos.com/story/2012/10/23/1149092/-Change-org-sells-out-progressive-movement}}</ref><ref name="karoli">{{cite web|url=http://crooksandliars.com/karoli/why-i-will-not-sign-another-changeorg-petit|title=Why I Will Not Sign Another Change.org Petition Ever|publisher=Crooks and Liars|date=2012-10-24|access-date=2015-09-30|archive-date=2015-10-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151001143207/http://crooksandliars.com/karoli/why-i-will-not-sign-another-changeorg-petit}}</ref>。結果，Change.org 被指控鼓勵進行騷擾，並放棄了最初吸引用戶的漸進式用戶基礎。當最初洩漏文件的僱員被解僱時，引起了更多爭議<ref name="karoli" />。在此更改後對站點失去興趣的用戶中，許多用戶表示很難從Change.org郵件列表中刪除<ref name="kos" />。

=== 出售個人資料 ===
Change.org 還被指控將用戶提供的個人數據出售給僱用其服務的第三方公司，從而以用戶為代價牟取金錢<ref name="changebiz"/>。

=== 用於熱門話題 ===
Change.org 請願書的主題已增長，其中包括與奧斯卡金像獎不同意以及從某些類型的咖啡中去除牛奶<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.latimes.com/food/dailydish/la-dd-starbucks-vegan-pumpkin-spice-latte-20130912-story.html|first=Jenn|last=Harris|title="First world problem": Vegans want Starbucks Pumpkin Spice Lattes too|work=Los Angeles Times|date=2013-09-12|access-date=2014-12-04|archive-date=2014-11-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141129234953/http://www.latimes.com/food/dailydish/la-dd-starbucks-vegan-pumpkin-spice-latte-20130912-story.html}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://blog.tradical360.com/7-dumbest-change-org-petitions-ever-created/ |first=Becky |last=Radolf |title=The 7 Dumbest Change.org Petitions Ever Created |publisher=Tradical |date=2014-03-07 |access-date=2014-12-04 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141217055129/http://blog.tradical360.com/7-dumbest-change-org-petitions-ever-created/ |archive-date=2014-12-17 }}</ref>。這些請願書的作者因關注「第一世界問題」而受到批評<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dallasobserver.com/news/apartment-tenants-start-changeorg-petition-over-package-delivery-really-7428094|title=Apartment tenants start Change.org petition over package delivery. Really|first=Amy|last=Martyn|publisher=Dallas Observer|date=2015-07-24|access-date=2016-11-19|archive-date=2016-11-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161120151636/http://www.dallasobserver.com/news/apartment-tenants-start-changeorg-petition-over-package-delivery-really-7428094}}</ref>。關於請願書內容的進一步辯論是在2014年11月，當時『馬丁·道布尼』 （Martin Daubney）稱其中一些為「bizarre」，並表示該網站被用來促進審查制度<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/men/thinking-man/11229136/Is-Change.org-just-a-weapon-of-censorship.html|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141115000138/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/men/thinking-man/11229136/Is-Change.org-just-a-weapon-of-censorship.html|url-status=dead|archive-date=2014-11-15|first=Martin|last=Daubney|title=Is Change.org just a weapon of censorship?|publisher=The Telegraph|date=2014-11-14|access-date=2014-12-04}}</ref>。作為回應，Change.org 傳播總監『約翰·考文垂』（John Coventry）為範圍廣泛的請願辯護，稱「人們在他們想要支持的方面做出了明智的選擇」<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/men/thinking-man/11230684/Its-wrong-to-accuse-Change.org-of-promoting-censorship.html|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141114212007/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/men/thinking-man/11230684/Its-wrong-to-accuse-Change.org-of-promoting-censorship.html|url-status=dead|archive-date=2014-11-14|first=John|last=Coventry|title=It's wrong to accuse Change.org of promoting censorship|publisher=The Telegraph|date=2014-11-14|access-date=2014-12-04}}</ref>。在接下來的一周裡，批評家指稱與媒體有關的請願比對「拯救『實際』生命」的請願更具關注<ref>{{cite web|url=http://things-that-matter.net/2014/11/20/how-can-a-petition-to-get-a-misogamist-pick-up-artist-refused-entry-to-the-uk-get-158000-signatures-and-our-petition-to-stop-the-home-office-just-leaving-people-to-drown-gets-3000-go-figure/|first=Ewan|last=Nicholson|title=How can a petition to get a misogynistic pick-up artist refused entry to the UK get 158,000 signatures and our petition to stop the Home Office just leaving people to drown gets 3000? Go figure.|publisher=Things That Matter|date=2014-11-20|access-date=2014-12-04|archive-date=2014-12-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141203204836/http://things-that-matter.net/2014/11/20/how-can-a-petition-to-get-a-misogamist-pick-up-artist-refused-entry-to-the-uk-get-158000-signatures-and-our-petition-to-stop-the-home-office-just-leaving-people-to-drown-gets-3000-go-figure/}}</ref>。

=== 捐赠用途 ===
Change.org也会请求联署人在签名的时候捐款。捐款不是强制的，但会让用户误以为捐款会用在主办方身上，或用来推动具体的请愿。根据网站的常见问题集，捐款金额“不设上限”，“Change.org会保管资金，用来更为广泛地‘传播’请愿书及支付自身的运营成本”<ref>{{cite web|url=https://africa.businessinsider.com/tech/changeorg-is-keeping-the-money-raised-through-its-record-breaking-george-floyd/6kp91hz|title=存档副本|access-date=2021-10-08|archive-date=2022-03-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220303145425/https://africa.businessinsider.com/tech/changeorg-is-keeping-the-money-raised-through-its-record-breaking-george-floyd/6kp91hz}}</ref>。2020年6月乔治·弗洛伊德之死引爆[[黑人的命也是命|黑人的命也是命]]起义后，140名Change.org前员工发表公开信，批评Change.org利用捐款打广告牌及数字广告，宣传请愿活动及网站，变相从黑人权利运动中获利<ref>{{cite web|url=https://medium.com/@blmopenletter/change-org-donate-to-blacklivesmatter-81273c5520ad|title=存档副本|access-date=2021-10-08|archive-date=2021-10-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211009125200/https://medium.com/@blmopenletter/change-org-donate-to-blacklivesmatter-81273c5520ad}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Holmes |first1=Aaron |title=Change.org doesn't donate the money raised through its record-breaking George Floyd petition — and some donors say they feel misled |url=https://www.businessinsider.com/change-org-george-floyd-donations-petition-keeps-money-2020-6 |website=Business Insider |access-date=2021-10-08 |archive-date=2020-06-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200604011934/https://www.businessinsider.com/change-org-george-floyd-donations-petition-keeps-money-2020-6 }}</ref>。

